I am a third year Ph.D student in Computer Science at Stanford University, co-advised by Prof. Peter Bailis and Prof. Philip Levis. I am a member of the Stanford DAWN project, and the Secure Internet of Things Project. I am broadly interested in efficient and effective data analytics for large-scale, machine generated data. My recent projects include automatic smoothing parameter selection for time series visualization and earthquake detection through computationally efficient time series similarity search.


I graduated from California Institute of Technology in 2015 with a B.S. in Computer Science. Before that, I attended Nanjing Foreign Language School in Nanjing, China.
